&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be responsible for the assessment and management of inpatients on a day-to-day basis, under consultant supervision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To participate in ward rounds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To ensure the effective delivery of care to patients in day case and inpatient theatres (some specialties)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To ensure the effective delivery of care to patients in outpatient clinics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To participate in multidisciplinary team meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To communicate effectively with clinical, nursing and other colleagues in the provision of patient care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To provide supervision and support to colleagues as appropriate for the grade.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To ensure all documentation is accurate and complete.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To follow Trust policies and procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be punctual and always report to/be available for work at the agreed start time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To attend local induction on commencement of duty in a new department or if working has not been undertaken in the Department in the previous 6 months.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
